-   Use utility-first classes for rapid development and consistent styling.
-   Create custom components with `@apply` directive for reusability.
-   Utilize responsive utility classes for mobile-friendly designs.
-   Implement dark mode using Tailwind's built-in classes.
-   Use Tailwind's pseudo-class variants for interactive elements.
-   Optimize CSS output by enabling JIT (Just-In-Time) mode.
-   Use Tailwind's configuration file to extend and customize the framework.
-   Implement accessibility features using Tailwind's accessibility classes.